        </div>

        <!-- The Downside -->
        <div class="text-center mt-12 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-amber-50 rounded-xl p-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto border border-amber-200">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">The Downside</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-left">
              Hedge posts can be naturally curvy due to their growth pattern. However, you can rotate the post to find a fairly straight side for wire attachment. Many experienced farmers optimize their fencing by alternating between hedge posts and steel T-posts, combining the longevity and strength of hedge with the cost-effectiveness of steel for maximum fence performance.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Call to Action -->
        <div class="text-center mt-12">
